        },
        "subject": "LU-1289 build: clean up module versioning",
        "message": "LU-1289 build: clean up module versioning\n\nClean up module versions to match Lustre build versions using\nLUSTRE_VERSION_STRING.  A few modules that are maintained\noutside the lustre tree (ptllnd, ralnd, mxlnd) keep their\nversion as-is in case it has some meaning to the developers.\nOtherwise, it would be possible to just fold the \"version\"\nparameter into the cfs_module() macro.\n\nNote that it is non-trivial to split out the module init\nand exit into separate module_init() and module_exit()\nwrappers due to the way that modules are handled in OSX.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I1c3fe5698c7f41d971a38225650597c916500c1e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
